decks.notes: This UR Aggro deck focuses on a fast-paced, aggressive strategy, utilizing cheap creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Slickshot Show-Off to deal damage quickly. The deck also includes burn spells such as Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart to control the board and finish off opponents. The use of Mishra's Bauble and Expressive Iteration provides card selection and velocity to keep up the pressure. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of creatures and burn spells for a swift victory.

This UR Aggro deck focuses on quickly deploying cheap threats like Monastery Swiftspear and Dragon's Rage Channeler while using efficient removal like Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart to control the board. Cards like Mishra's Bauble and Expressive Iteration help to filter through the deck and find additional threats. The deck aims to constantly apply pressure on the opponent, using spells like Mutagenic Growth and Violent Urge to pump up creatures for a quick win. Thundering Falls and Unholy Heat provide additional reach and removal options to close out the game.

This deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and disruptive spells, while also utilizing powerful cards like Teferi, Time Raveler to control the tempo of the game. By combining aggro elements with taxing effects like Prismatic Ending and Ephemerate, it seeks to disrupt the opponent's game plan and capitalize on its own synergies. The inclusion of powerful creatures like Solitude and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd give the deck resilience and a strong presence on the battlefield, allowing it to pressure the opponent effectively and close out games quickly.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan while deploying aggressive threats to quickly close out the game. It utilizes cards like Teferi, Time Raveler to control the opponent's spells, while creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury put pressure on the opponent. The deck also has a versatile removal package with cards like Prismatic Ending and Consign to Memory. Overall, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy while presenting a fast clock to secure victory.

This deck focuses on quickly ramping up mana and summoning powerful creatures like Primeval Titan to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and efficient combo. By utilizing cards like Amulet of Vigor and Simic Growth Chamber, the deck can consistently generate large amounts of mana and search for key lands to set up devastating combos. The goal is to assemble the right combination of cards to quickly bring out Primeval Titan and secure victory before the opponent has a chance to react effectively.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on aggressive creature plays and burn spells to quickly bring down the opponent's life total. With powerful creatures like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, backed up by burn spells like Galvanic Discharge and Goblin Bombardment, the deck aims to apply pressure and finish off the opponent quickly. The inclusion of cards like Ocelot Pride and Voice of Victory provide additional buffs and support to the creature lineup, making it a formidable force on the battlefield. Additionally, cards like Blood Moon and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer disrupt the opponent's game plan and further establish dominance.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on overwhelming the opponent with a combination of aggressive creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Ocelot Pride, along with powerful spells like Galvanic Discharge and Thraben Charm. The deck also includes Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to provide additional threats and win conditions. The inclusion of Goblin Bombardment and Voice of Victory adds versatility and disruption to the strategy, while cards like Solitude and Seasoned Pyromancer offer additional removal and card advantage to maintain momentum in the game.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly and aggressively deal damage to the opponent through a combination of cheap and efficient spells like Lightning Bolt, Lava Dart, and Mutagenic Growth, as well as creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Dragon's Rage Channeler. This UR Aggro deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain momentum throughout the game by utilizing cards like Expressive Iteration and Mishra's Bauble for card advantage and tempo plays. Additionally, the deck includes a mix of fetch lands and dual lands for mana fixing and consistency.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures, disruptive spells, and a mix of powerful enchantments to control the board and pressure the opponent. Key cards such as Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury provide early game pressure, while Teferi, Time Raveler and Prismatic Ending help control the opponent's plays. Consign to Memory and Quantum Riddler offer card advantage and additional disruption. Overall, the deck aims to apply pressure while disrupting the opponent's game plan, ultimately leading to a swift victory.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan while applying pressure through aggressive creatures like Orcish Bowmasters and Emperor of Bones. Thoughtseize and Teferi, Time Raveler are used to control the opponent's hand and spells, while Solitude provides removal. Ephemerate and Flickerwisp offer additional value by reusing powerful enter-the-battlefield abilities. The deck also includes a mix of lands to ensure consistent mana sources. Overall, the strategy revolves around a proactive aggro plan with disruptive elements to control the flow of the game and secure a win.

The deck focuses on quickly filling the graveyard with high-value creatures like Griselbrand and Atraxa, then using cards like Goryo's Vengeance and Quantum Riddler to bring them back onto the battlefield instantly. This combo allows for explosive plays and powerful board presence, while also disrupting the opponent's strategy with cards like Thoughtseize and Force of Negation. The deck aims to win the game through a combination of reanimation and control, overwhelming the opponent with powerful creatures and efficient removal spells.

This deck focuses on playing aggressive creatures in multiple colors to overwhelm the opponent quickly. It also includes powerful spells like Lightning Bolt and Leyline of Binding to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck includes a mix of cheap creatures, burn spells, and powerful finishers like Scion of Draco and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to close out the game. Additionally, the deck utilizes Leyline of the Guildpact to benefit from playing multiple colors and maximize its effectiveness.

This deck focuses on using powerful creatures and spells that can deal damage quickly and efficiently to overwhelm the opponent. With a mix of aggressive creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Scion of Draco, along with removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Stubborn Denial, the deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain board control. Leyline Binding and Leyline of the Guildpact help support the aggressive strategy by granting additional benefits. The deck also includes some versatile land cards to ensure consistent mana production and flexibility in spell casting.

The deck focuses on combining aggressive creatures with disruptive cards to control the game and overwhelm the opponent quickly. Cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Solitude provide strong threats, while cards like Teferi, Time Raveler and Prismatic Ending can disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck aims to keep the opponent off balance and take advantage of any openings to push for a win. By using a mix of aggression and disruption, the deck can adapt to different matchups and strategies in the Modern format.

The deck focuses on ramping up quickly to play powerful Eldrazi creatures, using cards like Utopia Sprawl and Eldrazi Temple to generate mana. Control elements are added with cards like Malevolent Rumble and Ugin's Labyrinth to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck also includes cards like Kozilek's Return and Herigast, Erupting Nullkite for additional removal and board control. Emrakul, the Promised End serves as a game-ending threat, while cards like Sire of Seven Deaths provide additional value and utility in the late game. Overall, the deck aims to control the game early and overwhelm the opponent with large, impactful creatures.

The deck focuses on aggressive play with a mix of creatures and spells to quickly deal damage to the opponent. It utilizes powerful creatures like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, along with support cards like Blood Moon and Thraben Charm to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The inclusion of Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Voice of Victory provide additional ways to pump up creatures for even more damage. The deck also has some control elements with cards like Static Prison and Witch Enchanter to deal with opposing threats.
